name: Float
summary:
The floating-point type in Julian language. This type implements IEEE-754 standard. It has a rought value range of approximately [-3.40282347E+38F, 3.40282347E+38F]. It can be cast to [int](Integer) with all precision lost.

float type can participate in arithmetic operations such as '+' and '*' and '/'. It can aslo be concatenated to string value with '+' operator in the literal form of this value.

int is a primitive type. Therefore it can only be assigned to a variable with same type or an [untyped](Any) variable.
